FuncDef: The display nat-policy template command displays information about a configured NAT policy template.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the name of the NAT template.
The value is a string of 1 to 31 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported. When double quotation marks are used around the string, spaces are allowed in the string.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The display nat-policy template command displays information about a configured NAT policy template.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
